name: Tiny Crystal
description: Scintillating dust. Sparkly, sparkly! Can be sold at a good price.

name: Average Crystal
description: A standard-size crystal from the Quetzal mines. Can be sold at a good price.

name: Scent
description: Eau de Pas-Tem. Sweet lavander notes with a warm black peppercorn heart. For some reason Temtem don't like it... Reduces untamed encounters for a while

name: Sea Salt
description: A fistful of fine "flor de sal" from the Turquesa salterns. These delicate and crumbly flakes are a universal seasoning. Can be sold at a good price.

name: Silicon Fragment
description: Bits and pieces of silicon, in high demand in Cipanku. Can be sold at a good price.

name: Silicon Shard
description: A standard-size piece of raw silicon, according to Nanto Labs specifications.. Can be sold at a good price.

name: Smoke Bomb
description: The best-loved Cipanki firework. The puff of smoke allows you to get back to the last visited Temporium or safe place.

name: TemCard
description: A card-like device used to capture and transport Temtem.

name: TemCard+
description: A high-end version of the TemCard, boasting an increased catch rate.

name: Balm
description: A balm made using a blend of Deizan healing herbs. Restores 25 HP.

name: Balm+
description: The traditional Omninesian healing salve, made of jungle roots. Restores 70 HP.

name: Vital Apple
description: An apple a day keeps the Temtem vet away! Restores 25%

name: Vital Durian
description: This spiky delight has an... interesting smell Restores 50%

name: Ether
description: The basic Stamina booster, popular Archipelago-wide. Restores 20 STA.

name: Ether+
description: "ConcentrEther", a more potent formula. Restores 45 STA.

name: Energetic Kiwi
description: Delicious Omninesian kiwis! Furry little bites of sweetness. Restores 25% STA.

name: Energetic Banana
description: Delicious Omninesian kiwis! Furry little bites of sweetness. Restores 50% STA.

name: Tonic
description: Although many Arburians use it as a mixer, it is actually a Kisiwan medicine. Restores 15 HP and 12 STA.

name: Tonic+
description: "A tonic, but even more so." Restores 42 HP and 27 STA.

name: Vigorous Loquat
description: These round golden beauties are packed with flavour. Restores 40% HP and 40% STA.

name: Revive
description: Miracle potion, potent enough to bring back a knocked out Temtem. Revives with  50% HP and STA.

name: Power Revive
description: Boost your Temtem's energy for the decisive final blow!. Revives with  25% HP and 100% STA.

name: Antidote
description: ALLERGY WARNING: Crystal dust, Gluten, Kalabyss feces. Heals a Poisoned Temtem.

name: Awakener
description: Ding-a-ling! Ding-a-ling! This handbell can wake up a rock! Heals an Asleep Temtem.

name: Cooler
description: When you want to chill and be cool at the same time. Heals a Burned Temtem.

name: Heater
description: Note: as of the current alpha (0.2.7) you can only obtain 2 Heater per play-through.

name: Enhancer Pineapple
description: Fresh, sweet and crunchy, these are a mainstay of the Nangui diet. Adds 20 TV to HP.

name: Enhancer Watermelon
description: Nothing beats a cool slice of watermelon on a hot day! Adds 20 TV to STA.

name: Enhancer Cherry
description: Ah, the cherry season has arrived! Adds 20 TV to SPD.

name: Enhancer Peach
description: Velvety and smooth, these are a true temptation. Adds 20 TV to ATK.

name: Enhancer Coconut
description: Hard to crack but sweet inside, just like a Crystle! Adds 20 TV to DEF.

name: Enhancer Mango
description: Soft and ripe, grown all along the Canopath. Adds 20 TV to SPATK.

name: Enhancer Papaya
description: A native species of Ulterior Omninesia, now widely farmed. Adds 20 TV to SPDEF.

name: Enhancer Avocado
description: These creamy delights make the best salads. Adds 50 TV to a random stat below 500 TV.

name: Weakener Lemon
description: Satisfyingly tart in lemonade, sorbet or on its own. Substracts 20 TV from HP.

name: Weakener Grapefruit
description: Widely grown both for fruit and wine. Substracts 20 TV from STA.

name: Weakener Kumquat
description: Juicy and scrumptious, harvested near Mokupuni. Substracts 20 TV from SPD.

name: Weakener Orange
description: Originally from Cipanku, now grown in every Denizan orchard. Substracts 20 TV from ATK.

name: Weakener Lime
description: Refreshingly zesty and citrusy! Substracts 20 TV from DEF.

name: Weakener Pomelo
description: One of the main exports from the Myrisles. Substracts 20 TV from SPATK.

name: Weakener Tangerine
description: Surely the best-loved Kisiwan produce! Substracts 20 TV from SPDEF.

name: Weakener Yuzu
description: A delicate jewel of Cipanki cuisine. Substracts 50 TV from a random stat over 0 TV.

name: Growth Enhancer
description: Genetic activators that speed up the growth of muscle tissue increasing a Temtem's level by 1.

name: Fertility Enhancer
description: A cocktail of cutting-edge drugs that increase a Temtem's fertility by 1.

name: Full Restore
description: The ultimate replenisher. Restores full HP, STA, and heals all Status Conditions.

name: Telomere Hack - SPD
description: This experimental genefix alters chromosomes in the Temtem DNA, adding 1 SV to SPD.

name: Telomere Hack - ATK
description: This experimental genefix alters chromosomes in the Temtem DNA, adding 1 SV to ATK.

name: Telomere Hack - SPATK
description: This experimental genefix alters chromosomes in the Temtem DNA, adding 1 SV to SPATK.

name: Telomere Hack - SPDEF
description: This experimental genefix alters chromosomes in the Temtem DNA, adding 1 SV to SPDEF.

name: Coward's Cloak
description: "Revolutionary cogno-cloak that allows the Temtem holding it to gain experience from battle without even taking part in it."

name: Decoy
description: "Useful distraction if you want to run away."

name: Fire Chip
description: Damage done by Fire Techniques is increased by 10%.

name: Four-leaf Clover
description: Increases the catch percentage when facing wild Temtem.

name: Hand Fan
description: Damage done by  Wind Techniques is increased by 10%.

name: Lightning Rod
description: Damage taken from  Electric Techniques is reduced by 20%.

name: Lure
description: Untamed Temtem can't ignore this delicious Lure and are forced to target the bearer. (Equipped Temtem will be the focus of all attacks in wild encounters)

name: Pillow
description: At the start of the turn, restores 10% of max hp of an  Asleep Temtem.

name: Proteins
description: Is obtained at the end of the Giant Banyan inside of the building. You must walk through the door. Inside are three item boxes: Proteins, a Green dye, and Lady Lottie's Diary.

name: Pansunscreen
description: Prevents the  Burned Status condition.

name: Talisman
description: "Prevents the Doomed Status condition."

name: Umbrella
description: "Damage taken from Water Techniques is reduced by 20%"

description: Reward from Find Kemal in Quetzal

name: Squeezer
description: Reward from Find Kemal in Quetzal

name: Sweatband
description: Reward from Cultist Hunt in Kupeleleza

name: Tucma Mask
description: Reward from Shipwrecked in Tucma! when first meeting Naolin

name: Snare
description: Reward from Blueprint Delivery

name: Chamomile
description: When entering the battlefield, removes stage changes.

name: Grease
description: Found at Wreck of the Narwhal

name: Shuine's Horn
description: Reward from Beached Narwhal

name: Vigor DNA Strand
description: This single-use DNA strand ensures the egg inherits the parent's HP and STA.

name: Mighty DNA Strand
description: This single-use DNA strand ensures the egg inherits the parent's ATK and SPATK

name: Immunity DNA Strand

name: Engineered DNA Strand

name: Archipelago Map
description: NEEDS DESCRIPTION

name: Surfboard
description: A fine board made by a master Denizan craftsman. Formerly Dojo Master Sophia's, now your very own.

name: Acid-proof Surfboard
description: A fine board Formerly Dojo Master Sophia's. It has been acid-proofed for use even in the most toxic of waters.

name: Crystal skates
description: A pair of crystal skates, ideal for maneuvering slippery surfaces.

name: Tempedia
description: Stores the data of seen and caught Temtem

name: Temessence phial
description: A vial of Temessence, enough to heal your whole squad. Replenish at HealTem machines and by certain characters.

name: Rock-hopping hook
description: Traditionally used for Tucmani sport and art of rock-hopping

name: Egg Timer
description: Tictoc... is it already time for your Temeggs to hatch? This handy timer will let you know when the little ones arrive.

name: Lift key
description: The Elevator Key is an item obtained from Rawiri after beating him in the Mokupuni Dojo.

name: Fort Windward key
description: An ancient-looking key to the dungeons of Windward Fort.

name: Airship ticket
description: A passenger ticket for the airship "Narwhal", plying the Arissola-Nanga-Uhuru route.

name: Blueprints
description: A series of detailed schematics by Oliana of MyrEng, to be delivered to the Guildmaster of Quetzal.

description: Talk to Sugey out in the Crater, Obtain 2 Water Samples, head back into Tucma Subsurface and inside are 2 nodes where you must collect the Water Samples A & B.

name: Water sample B
description: Talk to Sugey out in the Crater, Obtain 2 Water Samples, head back into Tucma Subsurface and inside are 2 nodes where you must collect the Water Samples A & B.

description: This is vial A and it's empty Sugey is expecting a sample from underground waters of Tucma
